.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2026" "version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a minimal command language interpreter that executes commands read from
the standard input. It is a simplified reimplementation of
.BR sh (1)
written as a school project at Holberton.
.PP
When invoked interactively,
.B simple_shell
displays a prompt
.RB ( $ )
and waits for the user to type a command. The line is split into words on
whitespace, the first word is looked up in the directories listed in the
.B PATH
environment variable, and the resulting program is executed in a child
process. The shell then waits for the child to terminate and prints a new
prompt.
.PP
When the standard input is not a terminal, the prompt is suppressed and
.B simple_shell
reads and executes commands one per line until end of file.
.SH BUILTINS
The following commands are implemented internally:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment, one variable per line.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B simple_shell
returns the exit status of the last command executed.
If the command cannot be found, the exit status is
.BR 127 .
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Run a command interactively:
.nf
.RS
$ /bin/ls
.RE
.fi
.PP
Run a command from a pipe:
.nf
.RS
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.RE
.fi
